                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.748,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 71722,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in Holt Civic Club and others against the City of Tuscaloosa will be announced by Mr. Justice Rehnquist."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.748,
                        "stop": 191.366,
                        "byte_start": 71722,
                        "byte_stop": 794164,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15141,
                            "name": "William H. Rehnquist",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_h_rehnquist",
                            "last_name": "Rehnquist",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2787,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 63612000,
                                    "date_end": 528094800,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2787"
                                },
                                {
                                    "id": 2788,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 1125723600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2788"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32786,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 46923,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_rehnquist.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12293,
                            "identifier": "william_h_rehnquist"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.748,
                                "stop": 24.466,
                                "byte_start": 71722,
                                "byte_stop": 126579,
                                "text": "Holt, Alabama is a rural unincorporated community located just outside the corporate limits of Tuscaloosa, Alabama but within Tuscaloosa\u0027s three-mile police jurisdiction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.466,
                                "stop": 60.654,
                                "byte_start": 126579,
                                "byte_stop": 271297,
                                "text": "Residents of Holt and an incorporated civic association brought this suit alleging that Alabama statutes subjecting police jurisdiction residents to Tuscaloosa\u0027s police and sanitary regulations to the criminal jurisdiction of Tuscaloosa\u0027s court and to the city\u0027s power to license businesses without also extending to police jurisdiction residents the right to vote in municipal elections violated their rights under the Equal Protection and Due Process Clauses of the Fourteenth Amendment of the constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.654,
                                "stop": 71.97,
                                "byte_start": 271297,
                                "byte_stop": 316646,
                                "text": "A three-judge District Court for the Northern District of Alabama concluded the Alabama statutes were not unconstitutional and granted appellee\u0027s motion to dismiss."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.97,
                                "stop": 81.486,
                                "byte_start": 316646,
                                "byte_stop": 354680,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the clerk we affirm the judgment of the District Court because Alabama\u0027s police jurisdiction statutes have stated application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.486,
                                "stop": 88.166,
                                "byte_start": 354680,
                                "byte_stop": 381430,
                                "text": "The three-judge District Court had jurisdiction to consider appellant\u0027s constitutional claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.166,
                                "stop": 101.295,
                                "byte_start": 381430,
                                "byte_stop": 433883,
                                "text": "On the merits, this Court\u0027s decisions have uniformly recognized that a government unit may legitimately restrict the right to participate in its political processes to those who reside within its borders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.295,
                                "stop": 112.036,
                                "byte_start": 433883,
                                "byte_stop": 476829,
                                "text": "Residents of Tuscaloosa\u0027s police jurisdiction do not reside within the city\u0027s corporate limits and therefore have no right to vote in municipal elections."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.036,
                                "stop": 122.505,
                                "byte_start": 476829,
                                "byte_stop": 518729,
                                "text": "Appellants are therefore not entitled to invoke the strict scrutiny standard which has been held to be applicable in previous voting rights decisions of this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.505,
                                "stop": 139.619,
                                "byte_start": 518729,
                                "byte_stop": 587170,
                                "text": "They are however like any other litigant entitled to claim that Alabama statute permitting Tuscaloosa to enforce some of its ordinances within the police jurisdiction denies them the equal protection of the laws secured by the Fourteenth Amendment to the United States constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.619,
                                "stop": 162.381,
                                "byte_start": 587170,
                                "byte_stop": 678285,
                                "text": "We conclude however that Alabama\u0027s police jurisdiction statutes are rationally related to the state\u0027s interest in affording municipalities some measure of control over activities conducted just beyond their corporate limits and ensuring that police jurisdiction residents do not go without basic municipal services such as police, fire, and health protection."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.381,
                                "stop": 179.886,
                                "byte_start": 678285,
                                "byte_stop": 748293,
                                "text": "Alabama statute here challenge does not therefore deny appellants the equal protection of the laws because it does not do so appellants likewise state no separate claim under Due Process Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment because they are denied the franchise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.886,
                                "stop": 184.741,
                                "byte_start": 748293,
                                "byte_stop": 767728,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stevens while joining the opinion of the Court has filed a concurring opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.741,
                                "stop": 191.366,
                                "byte_start": 767728,
                                "byte_stop": 794164,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Brennan joined by Mr. Justice White and Mr. Justice Marshall has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
